.TH "allocate_rcd_index" 9 "allocate_rcd_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
allocate_rcd_index \- allocate an rcd index from the rcd array
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" allocate_rcd_index
.BI "(struct hfi1_devdata *dd "  ","
.BI "struct hfi1_ctxtdata *rcd "  ","
.BI "u16 *index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dd" 12
pointer to a valid devdata structure
.IP "rcd" 12
rcd data structure to assign
.IP "index" 12
pointer to index that is allocated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find an empty index in the rcd array, and assign the given rcd to it.
If the array is full, we are EBUSY.
